<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,352,530,556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Erythria calvusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[359,453,530,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[468,611,530,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,192,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[214,1373,155,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3, dorsal view; 4 – 6, lateral view; 7 – 9, face; 1, 4, 7, Erythria calvusa sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8, E. cuspiprojecta sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9, E. euryprojecta sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number box="[536,582,530,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="1.4">1, 4</number>
, 
<number box="[595,611,530,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="11.05" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="7.1">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[624,699,530,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,340,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,301,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15. Erythria calvusa sp. nov. 10, pygofer side, lateral view; 11, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; 12, paramere, lateral view; 13, connective, dorsal view; 14, aedeagus, lateral view; 15, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281277/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">10–15</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,601,1057]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Body sandy beige. Pair of longitudinal brown streaks at sides of coronal suture and irregularly-shaped dark brown patches on pronotum, scutum with three blackish patches, scutellum dark brown. Fore wing sandy beige with veins semitransparent, hind wing weakly semitransparent with veins brownish-black (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1154,673,697]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,192,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[214,1373,155,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3, dorsal view; 4 – 6, lateral view; 7 – 9, face; 1, 4, 7, Erythria calvusa sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8, E. cuspiprojecta sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9, E. euryprojecta sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number box="[1109,1154,673,697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="1.4">1, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,601,1057]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[201,368,709,733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer with sclerotized appendage at hind upper angle (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1144,709,733]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,340,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,301,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15. Erythria calvusa sp. nov. 10, pygofer side, lateral view; 11, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; 12, paramere, lateral view; 13, connective, dorsal view; 14, aedeagus, lateral view; 15, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281277/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number box="[1113,1144,709,733]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broad, nearly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[360,446,745,769]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,340,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,301,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15. Erythria calvusa sp. nov. 10, pygofer side, lateral view; 11, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; 12, paramere, lateral view; 13, connective, dorsal view; 14, aedeagus, lateral view; 15, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281277/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number box="[417,446,745,769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apical extension of paramere short, curved laterad apically (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1271,745,769]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,340,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,301,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15. Erythria calvusa sp. nov. 10, pygofer side, lateral view; 11, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; 12, paramere, lateral view; 13, connective, dorsal view; 14, aedeagus, lateral view; 15, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281277/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number box="[1240,1271,745,769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Penis compressed, tapering apically and proximad (
<figureCitation box="[613,749,781,805]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,340,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,301,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15. Erythria calvusa sp. nov. 10, pygofer side, lateral view; 11, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; 12, paramere, lateral view; 13, connective, dorsal view; 14, aedeagus, lateral view; 15, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281277/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number box="[676,749,781,805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="14.15">14, 15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonopore ventral.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,601,1057]" box="[201,719,817,841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[201,352,818,841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Measurement</emphasis>
: Male 3.2 mm (including wing).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
